The Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice,  Abubakar Malami (SAN), says the Federal Government will be guided by public interest in complying with a court calling for recovery of pensions paid to former governors who are serving senators and ministers. A Federal High Court in Lagos had on Wednesday while delivering judgment in the suit filed by SERAP, ordered former governors to refund all monies they collected as pensions after leaving their offices. Malami, through his media aide, Umar Gwandu, said: “We will work and be guided by the legalities of the case the dictates of justice and public interest in complying with the judgment”. Court orders FG to recover pensions collected by Akpabio, Saraki, Amaechi, Kwankwaso, others Amaechi denies collecting pension from Rivers govt Ex-governors mum as court orders recovery of pensions